{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":420,"text":"In the 1600s, there were so many\nright whales in Cape Cod Bay"},{"time":4914,"text":"off the east coast of the U.S."},{"time":6741,"text":"that apparently you could\nwalk across their backs"},{"time":10389,"text":"from one end of the bay to the other."},{"time":13234,"text":"Today, they number in the hundreds,\nand they're endangered."},{"time":16573,"text":"Like them, many species of whales\nsaw their numbers drastically reduced"},{"time":21728,"text":"by 200 years of whaling,"},{"time":24170,"text":"where they were hunted and killed\nfor their whale meat, oil and whale bone."}]},{"cues":[{"time":31009,"text":"We only have whales in our waters today"},{"time":33412,"text":"because of the Save the Whales\nmovement of the '70s."},{"time":37057,"text":"It was instrumental in stopping\ncommercial whaling,"},{"time":40455,"text":"and was built on the idea that\nif we couldn't save whales,"},{"time":44227,"text":"what could we save?"},{"time":46154,"text":"It was ultimately a test\nof our political ability"},{"time":49080,"text":"to halt environmental destruction."},{"time":52683,"text":"So in the early '80s, there was\na ban on commercial whaling"},{"time":56236,"text":"that came into force\nas a result of this campaign."},{"time":59951,"text":"Whales in our waters are still\nlow in numbers, however,"},{"time":62760,"text":"because they do face a range\nof other human-induced threats."}]},{"cues":[{"time":67489,"text":"Unfortunately, many people still think\nthat whale conservationists like myself"},{"time":75136,"text":"do what we do only because these creatures\nare charismatic and beautiful."},{"time":81939,"text":"This is actually a disservice,"},{"time":84025,"text":"because whales are ecosystem engineers."},{"time":88499,"text":"They help maintain the stability\nand health of the oceans,"},{"time":92872,"text":"and even provide services\nto human society."}]},{"cues":[{"time":97299,"text":"So let's talk about why\nsaving whales is critical"},{"time":101275,"text":"to the resiliency of the oceans."},{"time":104806,"text":"It boils down to two main things:"},{"time":109334,"text":"whale poop and rotting carcasses."}]},{"cues":[{"time":112546,"text":"As whales dive to the depths to feed\nand come up to the surface to breathe,"},{"time":118012,"text":"they actually release these\nenormous fecal plumes."},{"time":121918,"text":"This whale pump, as it's called,\n"},{"time":123662,"text":"actually brings essential limiting \nnutrients from the depths"},{"time":126955,"text":"to the surface waters where they \nstimulate the growth of phytoplankton,"},{"time":130975,"text":"which forms the base\nof all marine food chains."},{"time":134422,"text":"So really, having more whales\nin the oceans pooping"},{"time":137127,"text":"is really beneficial\nto the entire ecosystem."}]},{"cues":[{"time":141208,"text":"Whales are also known to undertake some \nof the longest migrations of all mammals."},{"time":146760,"text":"Gray whales off America\nmigrate 16,000 kilometers"},{"time":152707,"text":"between productive feeding areas and less\nproductive calving, or birthing, areas"},{"time":158812,"text":"and back every year."},{"time":161902,"text":"As they do so, they transport fertilizer\nin the form of their feces"},{"time":166886,"text":"from places that have it\nto places that need it."},{"time":170676,"text":"So clearly, whales are really\nimportant in nutrient cycling,"},{"time":174115,"text":"both horizontally and vertically,\nthrough the oceans."}]},{"cues":[{"time":177807,"text":"But what's really cool is that they're \nalso really important after they're dead."},{"time":184466,"text":"Whale carcasses are some of \nthe largest form of detritus"},{"time":188559,"text":"to fall from the ocean's surface, \nand they're called whale fall."},{"time":193409,"text":"As these carcasses sink,"},{"time":195466,"text":"they provide a feast\nto some 400-odd species,"},{"time":198495,"text":"including the eel-shaped, slime-producing \nhagfish."},{"time":203021,"text":"So over the 200 years of whaling,"},{"time":205154,"text":"when we were busy killing and removing\nthese carcasses from the oceans,"},{"time":209524,"text":"we likely altered the rate and geographic \ndistribution of these whale falls"},{"time":215246,"text":"that would descend into deep oceans,"},{"time":217563,"text":"and as a result, probably led\nto a number of extinctions"},{"time":221254,"text":"of species that were most specialized"},{"time":223392,"text":"and dependent on these carcasses\nfor their survival."}]},{"cues":[{"time":227876,"text":"Whale carcasses are also known\nto transport about 190,000 tons of carbon,"},{"time":235808,"text":"which is the equivalent of that produced"},{"time":238106,"text":"by 80,000 cars per year"},{"time":241171,"text":"from the atmosphere to the deep oceans,"},{"time":244000,"text":"and the deep oceans\nare what we call \"carbon sinks,\""},{"time":247510,"text":"because they trap and hold\nexcess carbon from the atmosphere,"},{"time":251573,"text":"and therefore help\nto delay global warming."},{"time":255789,"text":"Sometimes these carcasses\nalso wash up on beaches"},{"time":259468,"text":"and provide a meal to a number\nof predatory species on land."}]},{"cues":[{"time":264540,"text":"The 200 years of whaling\nwas clearly detrimental"},{"time":268464,"text":"and caused a reduction\nin the populations of whales"},{"time":271356,"text":"between 60 to 90 percent."},{"time":274476,"text":"Clearly, the Save the Whales movement"},{"time":276302,"text":"was instrumental in preventing\ncommercial whaling from going on,"},{"time":280713,"text":"but we need to revise this."},{"time":283854,"text":"We need to address the more modern,\npressing problems that these whales face"},{"time":288608,"text":"in our waters today."},{"time":290349,"text":"Amongst other things, we need to stop them"},{"time":292482,"text":"from getting plowed down by container \nships when they're in their feeding areas,"},{"time":297187,"text":"and stop them from getting\nentangled in fishing nets"},{"time":299985,"text":"as they float around in the ocean."},{"time":302469,"text":"We also need to learn to contextualize\nour conservation messages,"},{"time":306839,"text":"so people really understand the true \necosystem value of these creatures."}]},{"cues":[{"time":313985,"text":"So, let's save the whales again,"},{"time":318142,"text":"but this time, let's not just \ndo it for their sake."},{"time":322275,"text":"Let's also do it for ours."}]},{"cues":[{"time":324806,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":327151,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}